reviewText: I've enjoyed my personal visits to Alaska in 1985, 1992, 1993, 1994, and 1995.  These  DVDs provide some interesting video scenes of Alaska.  There are five DVDs  with over 10 hours of recording.  Some of the contents on the DVDs include the following:  Kenai River, King Season, Bears & Salmon, Juneau, Kachemak Bay, Soldotna, and Seldovia.

I purchased this for a gift for Christmas. My mother is loving it, as it reminds her of her trip to Alaska with her two brothers. Great way to package DVD's.  She liked it better than the National Geographic set we got her the year before.
Ok it says it shows all this stuff on multiple DVD's but this is a rather poor documentary version. Almost grainy video. There's a single DVD version that's gotta be better than this.
